<h1>Render modes</h1>

<p>
    Every page is server-rendered by default (SSR). Add a magic comment at the top of the
    file to opt into something else.
</p>

<h2>Static (SSG)</h2>
<pre><code>@@* @@nxt:static *@@

&lt;h1&gt;About&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Generated once at build time.&lt;/p&gt;</code></pre>

<p>
    <code>nxt build</code> walks every static-marked route and writes the HTML to
    <code>wwwroot/_nxt_static/&lt;path&gt;.html</code>. Requests hit the cache directly —
    no rendering work per request.
</p>

<h2>Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR)</h2>
<pre><code>@@* @@nxt:revalidate=30 *@@

&lt;p&gt;Built at: @@DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("O")&lt;/p&gt;</code></pre>

<p>
    Like static, but every <code>N</code> seconds the page is silently re-rendered in the
    background. Readers always get cached HTML (fast); the cache stays warm.
</p>

<h2>Interactive Server (Blazor Server)</h2>
<pre><code>@@* @@nxt:interactive-server *@@

&lt;button @@onclick="() =&gt; count++"&gt;Clicked @@count times&lt;/button&gt;

@@code &#123; int count; &#125;</code></pre>

<p>
    The page is SSR'd, then a SignalR connection takes over so <code>@@onclick</code>,
    state changes, and re-renders happen interactively. Requires <code>UseAntiforgery</code>
    (Nxt wires it for you).
</p>

<h2>Interactive WebAssembly</h2>
<p>
    The component must live in a sibling project built with
    <code>Microsoft.NET.Sdk.BlazorWebAssembly</code>, otherwise its DLL isn't shipped to the
    browser. The server then references that project and chains
    <code>AddInteractiveWebAssemblyRenderMode()</code>
    + <code>AddAdditionalAssemblies(typeof(MyClientComponent).Assembly)</code>:
</p>
<pre><code>await NxtHost.RunAsync(args, opts =&gt;
&#123;
    opts.ConfigureServices = b =&gt;
        b.Services.AddRazorComponents().AddInteractiveWebAssemblyComponents();

    opts.ConfigureRazorEndpoints = blazor =&gt;
        blazor.AddInteractiveWebAssemblyRenderMode()
              .AddAdditionalAssemblies(typeof(MyApp.Client.Counter).Assembly);
&#125;);</code></pre>

<p>Then in a server page, reference the client component with the render mode:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;Counter @@rendermode="InteractiveWebAssembly" /&gt;</code></pre>

<p>See <a href="/docs/wasm">Blazor WebAssembly</a> for the full setup.</p>
